Treasury's Powell to Take
   Glauber's Post, Aides Say
Mr. Glauber's former special assistant, John Hauge, is
expected to fill a new post on the international side of the
Treasury, that of deputy assistant secretary for Eastern
Europe and the former Soviet Union.
   Charles Schotta, who has been deputy assistant secretary
for East European, Soviet and Middle East policy, will
oversee Middle East and energy policy.